  "prompt": "Who is the best cardiologist doctors in Delhi?",
  "response": "There are many highly skilled cardiologists in Delhi, but the \"best\" doctor can vary depending on specific needs, such as the type of cardiac issue, personal preferences, and accessibility. Here are some renowned cardiologists and hospitals in Delhi known for their expertise in cardiology:\n\n### Top Cardiologists in Delhi:\n1. **Dr. Ashok Seth**  \n   - Chairman of Fortis Escorts Heart Institute, New Delhi.  \n   - Renowned for his expertise in interventional cardiology and angioplasty.  \n   - Recipient of numerous national and international awards.  \n\n2. **Dr. Naresh Trehan**  \n   - Chairman and Managing Director of Medanta - The Medicity, Gurgaon (near Delhi).  \n   - A pioneer in cardiac surgery and minimally invasive heart surgery.  \n\n3. **Dr. K.K. Talwar**  \n   - Senior Consultant Cardiologist at Max Super Speciality Hospital, Saket.  \n   - Former Director of PGIMER, Chandigarh.  \n\n4. **Dr. Manjinder Sandhu**  \n   - Director of Cardiology at Artemis Hospital, Gurgaon.  \n   - Specializes in preventive cardiology and heart failure management.  \n\n5. **Dr. S.S. Kothari**  \n   - Senior Consultant Cardiologist at AIIMS (All India Institute of Medical Sciences), New Delhi.  \n   - Expert in pediatric and adult cardiology.  \n\n### Top Hospitals for Cardiology in Delhi:\n1. **Fortis Escorts Heart Institute (FEHI), Okhla**  \n   - Known for its advanced cardiac care and state-of-the-art facilities.  \n\n2. **Max Super Speciality Hospital, Saket**  \n   - Offers comprehensive cardiac care, including surgeries and interventions.  \n\n3. **Medanta - The Medicity, Gurgaon**  \n   - A premier hospital with a world-class cardiology department.  \n\n4. **All India Institute of Medical Sciences (AIIMS), New Delhi**  \n   - Renowned for its expertise in cardiology and cardiac research.  \n\n5. **Apollo Hospitals, Greams Road, Chennai (with branches in Delhi)**  \n   - A leading name in cardiac care across India.  \n\nWhen choosing a cardiologist, consider factors like the doctor\u2019s experience, hospital facilities, patient reviews, and proximity. It\u2019s always best to consult with a specialist who aligns with your specific needs.",
